doc.after: Order Passeriformes Family Fringillidae Finches are seed eating passerines They are small to moderately large and have strong usually conical and sometimes very large beaks All have twelve tail feathers and nine primaries They have a bouncing flight with alternating bouts of flapping and gliding on closed wings and most sing well
